Gender Sensitivity and Harassment Of Woman At Workplace (Prevention
Prohibition And Redressal) Act 2013- POSH


20th December 2018 - Mumbai:- Ramada Plaza Palm Grove

20th December 2018 - Bangalore:- Royal Orchid

21st December 2018 - Chennai:- Abu Sarovar

21st December 2018 - Ahmedabad:- Comfort Inn 

22nd December 2018 - Delhi:- Park Plaza 

22nd December 2018 - Hyderabad:- Aditya Park 

24th December 2018 - Kolkata:- Radisson 

24th December 2018 - Pune:- Sagar Plaza 


Overview

Providing a safe work environment, gender sensitization and preventing all
forms of sexual harassment is a mandate by law. To ensure that the workplace
is safe and secure, the employees, managers, leaders of an organization must
be aware of what is and isn't sexual harassment and what steps need to be
taken to prevent, prohibit and address any forms of sexual harassment.
Non-compliance will lead to hefty penalties, including cancellation of
license

Who should attend?

Employees, Managers, Leaders, HR, Internal Committee members, anyone who
wants to refresh their knowledge of recent updates in the law, or wants to
understand a practical and sensitive approach to dealing with the situation


 
Agenda

- Sexual Harassment - History & Current state, Acts with supports SH,
Includes Vishakha guidelines (1997), Sexual Harassment of women at workplace
(prevention, prohibition and redressal) act (2013).  

- Qualifiers of Sexual Harassment

- Terminologies - aggrieved women, workplace, extended workplace, employer,
Internal Committee, Local Committee

- Employer's obligation 

- What is Internal Committee

- Who can be an external member

- Population covered under Sexual Harassment for an Organization

- Hostile and Quid pro quo work environments

- Employer's Sexual Harassment escalation matrix

- Determination of compensation interim action during inquiry

- Dealing with false malicious complaint

- Penalties 

- IPC provisions 

- Case Study - differentiate personal & professional relationship to
identify Sexual Harassment

- Preventive steps an employer must take

- FAQ's - General queries, IC/ LC/ External member related queries/ Training
and awareness related queries


Timings: 10:00 am - 5:00 pm, Registration begins at 9:30 am*

